peopleAlsoAsk.question: How much is my old china worth?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Online research: Start by searching for the manufacturer and pattern of your china on online marketplaces like eBay and Etsy, as well as antique shops' websites. Look for items similar to yours and note their prices. This can give you an idea of the current market value.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Is there a market for old china dishes?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Depending on the pattern, condition and current supply and demand, you can make a few hundred dollars when you sell Nana's china plates or perhaps more than $1,000. In most cases, however, what was sentimentally valuable china to your family is worth $5 to $20 a plate.
